Cloud Monitoring and Alerting Using AWS CloudWatch
Project Overview

This project demonstrates how to monitor cloud resources and configure automated alerts using AWS CloudWatch. An EC2 instance is monitored for CPU utilization, and alerts are triggered using Amazon SNS when CPU usage crosses a defined threshold. The project validates real-time monitoring, alerting, and recovery behavior.

Architecture Explanation

An EC2 instance continuously sends performance metrics such as CPU utilization to Amazon CloudWatch. CloudWatch evaluates these metrics against a predefined threshold. When the threshold is breached, CloudWatch triggers an alarm and sends a notification through Amazon SNS to the configured email address. Once CPU usage returns to normal, the alarm automatically resets to the OK state.

AWS Services Used

Amazon EC2 – Compute resource being monitored

Amazon CloudWatch – Monitoring and alerting service

Amazon SNS – Notification service for alerts

Monitoring Configuration

Metric Monitored: CPUUtilization

Statistic: Average

Threshold: ≥ 35% CPU usage

Period: 1 minute

Evaluation Periods: 2 out of 2

Notification Method: SNS Email

This configuration ensures fast and reliable alert triggering during sustained CPU load.

Alerting Workflow

EC2 instance runs under normal conditions (Alarm state: OK)

CPU-intensive workload is generated on the instance

CPU utilization exceeds 35% for 2 consecutive minutes

CloudWatch alarm transitions to ALARM state

SNS sends email notification

Load is stopped
Recovery Verification

After stopping the CPU load, the alarm automatically returned to the OK state, confirming that the monitoring and alerting lifecycle works as expected.
CPU usage returns to normal

Alarm transitions back to OK state
